Steps to Reproduce:

1. I'm a theme author, and I noticed some items in scss variable declartions are all scoped to `token scss meta set variable`, including font names and punctuation, making them impossible to color them to match punctuation and font names elsewhere in scss files -- since they are the same scope as the variables themselves (maroon in [my theme](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=smlombardi.theme-tesla))

![screen shot 2016-11-28 at 3 57 31 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/835148/20685770/c1556648-b583-11e6-91f1-d780667955d7.jpg)

The code used here is:
```scss
$font-family-sans-serif: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-serif: Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif;
$font-family-base: $font-family-sans-serif;
$font-family-monospace: Menlo, Consolas, Monaco, 'Courier New', monospace;
$font-family-ps-light: 'PrecisionSans_W_Lt', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-light-italic: 'PrecisionSans_W_LtIt', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-regular: 'PrecisionSans_W_Rg', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-regular-italic: 'PrecisionSans_W_RgIt', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-medium: 'PrecisionSans_W_Md', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-medium-italic: 'PrecisionSans_W_MdIt', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-bold: 'PrecisionSans_W_Bd', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$font-family-ps-bold-italic: 'PrecisionSans_W_BdIt', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
$headings-font-weight: normal;
$headings-line-height: 1.1;
$headings-color: inherit;
$btn-font-weight: normal;
```
